# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok suspected taliban militants ambushed a police chief in southern afghanistan , killing four of his officers and abducting two more , an official said wednesday .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG2 (o / official)))
      :ARG1 (a / ambush-01
            :ARG0 (m / militant
                  :ARG0-of (h2 / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG1 (c / criminal-organization
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "Taliban"))
                        :ARG2 m)
                  :ARG1-of (s2 / suspect-01)))
      :ARG1 (p2 / person
            :ARG0-of (h3 / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (p3 / police)
                  :ARG2 (c2 / chief)))
      :location (s3 / south
            :part-of (c3 / country
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "Afghanistan")))
      :ARG0-of (c4 / cause-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (k / kill-01
                        :ARG0 m
                        :ARG1 (p4 / person
                              :quant 4
                              :ARG0-of (h4 / have-org-role-91
                                    :ARG1 p3
                                    :ARG2 (o2 / officer))))
                  :op2 (a3 / abduct-01
                        :ARG0 m
                        :ARG1 (p5 / person
                              :quant 2
                              :mod (m2 / more)))))
      :time (w / wednesday))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                  :op1 "Jiangxi")

                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "China")))
      :ARG1 (s / system

                  :ARG1 (ii / internet)))
      :location (b / bar
            :mod (c2 / cyber))

            :ARG0 p
            :ARG2 (p2 / prevent-01
                  :ARG0 p
                  :ARG1 (ii2 / ill-01
                        :ARG1-of (p3 / possible-01)))))

                  :time-of s))
      :weekday (t2 / thursday))

                                    :domain v))))))
